 11 var drawing = null;
 12 var globalMap = new java.util.HashMap(47);

 16 /**
 17  * @private
 18  * Initializes the SVG document.
 19  * It adjusts the viewBox to be proportional with
 20  * the width and height of the drawing.
 21  * If width or height are zero, it will call a
 22  * user-defined function, calculateDimensions() to
 23  * provide width and height in the variable container.
 24  * It looks for a variable name "doc_padding" to define
 25  * the padding around the drawn object.  If not specified,
 26  * the padding defaults to 12 inches (or equivalent mm).
 27  * It also initializes the command interface which 
 28  * enables java code to call javascript functions. 
 29  * @return
 30  */
 31 function initDoc()
 32 {
 33 try{
 34 debug = g("f_debug") == "true";
 35 trace("initDoc()");
 36 
 37 var nested = g("f_nested") == "true";
 38 
 39 
 40 var w = gN("width");
 41 var h = gN("height");
 42 
 43 
 44 if(w === 0 || h === 0)
 45 {
 46 	try
 47 	{
 48 		calculateDimensions();
 49 	}
 50 	catch(notfound){}
 51 	w = gN("width");
 52 	h = gN("height");
 53 }
 54 if(w == 0)
 55 {
 56 	w = gN("f_width");
 57 }
 58 if(h == 0)
 59 {
 60 	h = gN("f_height");
 61 }
 62 var p = nested ? 0:(g("f_um")=="mm"?inchesToMM(12):12);
 63 
 64 var wPage = g("f_docWidth");
 65 var hPage = g("f_docHeight");
 66 var fixedSize = g("f_fixedSize") == "true";	
 67 
 68 
 69 if(w == 0)
 70 	w = 120;
 71 if(h == 0)
 72 	h = 96;
 73 
 74 	var docWidthPX = s("docWidthPX",wPage);
 75 	var docHeightPX = s("docHeightPX",hPage);
 76 	var docWidthUM = s("docWidthUM", w);
 77 	var docHeightUM = s("docHeightUM", h);
 78 	
 79 	var tn = s("f_tn",(docWidthPX <= 120 && docHeightPX <= 120)?"true":"false") == "true";
 80 
 81 	var doc = drawing.getDocumentElement();
 82 	doc.setAttribute("viewBox",(nested ? "-.0625 -.0625 "+ (w+.125) + " " + (h+.125) :"-"+p+" -"+p+" "+ (w+(2*p)) + " " + (h+(2*p))));
 83 	
 84 	if(fixedSize)
 85 	{
 86 		doc.setAttribute("width",wPage+"px");
 87 		doc.setAttribute("height",hPage+"px");
 88 	}
 89 	else
 90 	{
 91 		if(((h+p)/hPage) < ((w+p)/wPage))
 92 		{
 93 			var docH = wPage*((h+p)/(w+p));
 94 			doc.setAttribute("width",wPage+"px");
 95 			doc.setAttribute("height",docH+"px");
 96 		}
 97 		else
 98 		{
 99 			var docW = hPage*((w+p)/(h+p));
100 			doc.setAttribute("width",docW+"px");
101 			doc.setAttribute("height",hPage+"px");
102 		}
103 	}
104 	var winGrp = drawing.getElementById("window");
105 	if(winGrp == null)
106 	{
107 		winGrp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
108 		winGrp.setAttribute("id","window");
109 		drawing.getDocumentElement().appendChild(winGrp);
110 	}
111 	trace("calling initCommandInterface()");
112 	initCommandInterface();
113 	trace("returning from initCommandInterface()");
114 	
115 	if(applet)
116 	{
117 			applet.registerLite(g("f_idPrefix")+"this","0","0",w+"",h+"",null);
118 	}
119 	
120 }	
121 catch(e)
122 {
123 	alertUser("Exception:  initDoc()");
124 	alertUser(e);
125 	trace(e);
126 }		
127 } 
128

130 /**
131  * Convert inches to millimeters.
132  * @param i decimal inches
133  * @return	decimal millimeters
134  */
135 function inchesToMM(i)
136 {
137 trace("inchesToMM(" + i + ")");
138 	return Math.round(i*25.4);
139 }
140 
141 /**
142  * @private
143  * Creates a mechanism that enables java to
144  * call into the javascript.
145  * 
146  * @return void
147  */
148 function initCommandInterface()
149 {
150 try{
151 	var text = drawing.getElementById("java2jsDummyText");
152                                        
153 	if(text == null)
154 	{
155   		text= drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"text");
156 		text.setAttribute("id","java2jsDummyText");
157    		text.setAttribute("x", "0");
158   		text.setAttribute("y", "0");
159   		text.setAttribute("visibility", "hidden");
160 
161 		// Create separate cmd element because we don't want
162 		// setting the cmd to prematurely trigger it's own execution.
163 		// I.e. we can better control the timing.
164 		var cmd= drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"text");
165 		cmd.setAttribute("id","java2jsCommand");
166    		cmd.setAttribute("x", "0");
167   		cmd.setAttribute("y", "0");
168   		cmd.setAttribute("visibility", "hidden");
169 		var cmdContent = drawing.createTextNode(";");
170 		cmd.appendChild(cmdContent);
171   
172   		var svgRoot = drawing.getDocumentElement();
173   		svgRoot.appendChild(text);
174  		svgRoot.appendChild(cmd);
175   
176 		text.addEventListener("DOMCharacterDataModified", executeCmd, false); 
177 	}
178 	
179 }
180 catch(e)
181 {
182 	alertUser("Exception thrown: initCommandInterface()");
183 	alertUser(e);
184 	
185 }
186 
187 } 
188 
189 /**
190  * Externally (from java) execute javascript commands. 
191  * @return
192  */
193 function executeCmd()
194 {
195 var cmdScript=getText("java2jsCommand");
196 trace("executeCmd("+cmdScript+")");
197 try{
198 	eval(cmdScript);
199 	trace("eval completed");
200 }
201 catch(e)
202 {
203 	trace("Exception thrown: executeCmd(" + cmdScript + ")");
204 	trace(e);
205 	
206 }
207 }

209 /**
210  * Get a value from the variable container.
211  * 
212  * @param id String name of variable.
213  * @return String value of variable or null if not found.
214  */
215 function g(id)
216 {
217 	if(applet != null)
218 	{
219 		return applet.getVar(id);
220 	}
221 	return globalMap.get(id);
222 }	
223 
224 /**
225  * Get a numeric value from the variable container.
226  * Same as g() except it will always coerce the value
227  * to a number.  If the value is not a number, or it's not
228  * found in the container, it returns 0.
229  * @param id String name of variable.
230  * @return decimal
231  */
232 function gN(id)
233 {
234 	var n;
235 	if(applet != null)
236 	{
237 		n = applet.getVar(id);
238 	}
239 	else
240 	{
241 		n = globalMap.get(id);
242 	}
243 	if(n === null || isNaN(n))
244 		return 0
245 	return n-0;
246 }	
247 
248 /**
249  * Set a value in the variable container.
250  *  
251  * @param id  String name of variable
252  * @param value  untyped value to assign.
253  * @return untyped value assigned
254  */
255 function s(id,value)
256 {
257 
258 	if(applet)
259 	{
260 		applet.setVar(id,value);
261 	}
262 	else
263 	{
264 		globalMap.put(id, new java.lang.String(value));
265 		trace("set('"+id+"','"+value+"')");
266 		
267 	}
268 	
269 	return value;
270 }
271 /**
272  * Initializes a value in the variable container, and the original
273  * value container.  Not the same as s(...) because it doesn't 
274  * update the original value container.  The system compares
275  * the original value with the current value to determine if
276  * a configuration value should be updated.
277  * $initialize generates the code to initialize each of the
278  * drawing variables.
279  * 
280  * @param id String name of variable.
281  * @param value
282  * @return
283  */
284 function init(id,value)
285 {
286 
287 	if(applet)
288 	{
289 		applet.initVar(id,value);
290 	}
291 	else
292 	{
293 		globalMap.put(id,new java.lang.String(value));
294 		trace("init('"+id+"','"+value+"')");
295 	}
296 	
297 	return value;
298 }

300 /**
301  * Write text to systemOut.log (i.e. java console in applet).
302  * Use this function for debugging your scripts.
303  * 
304  * @param text
305  * @return void
306  */
307 function trace(text)
308 {
309 	if(debug == false) return;
310 	if(applet != null)
311 		applet.log(text);
312 	else
313 		System.out.println(text);
314 }

317  * Display text to the user.
318  * @param text
319  * @return void
320  */
321 function alertUser(text)
322 {
323 	alert(text);
324 }

326 /**
327  * Remove leading and trailing whitespace for a String.
328  * 
329  * @param input String to be trimmed.
330  * @return
331  */
332 function trim(input)
333 {
334 	var s = new java.lang.String(input);
335 	return s.trim();
336 }

341 /**
342  * Start dragging a vertical grille element
343  * @param evt Event
344  * @return void
345  */
346 function startDragX(evt)
347 {
348 	if(applet==null)
349 		return;
350 	
351 	var rightClick =  (evt.which && evt.which == 3)
352 						||
353 						(evt.button && evt.button == 2);
354 
355 	var el = evt.getTarget();
356 	dragObj = el;
357 	dragOffset = getX(evt) - el.getAttribute("x");  
358 	dragType = "X";
359 	
360 		applet.startDragX(el.id,"");
361 
362 }

398 /**
399  * Drag and move a grille element.
400  * @param evt Event
401  * @return void
402  */
403 function drag(evt)
404 {
405 	
406 	if(dragObj == null)
407 		return;
408 		
409 
410 		
411 	switch(dragType)
412 	{
413 		case 'X':
414 			dragObj.setAttribute("x",getX(evt)-dragOffset);
415 			applet.dragX(dragObj.id);
416 			break;
417 		case 'Y':
418 			dragObj.setAttribute("y",getY(evt)-dragOffset);
419 			applet.dragY(dragObj.id);
420 			break;
421 		default: break;
422 	}
423 }
424 
425 
426 /**
427  * Drop a grille element.
428  * @param evt Event
429  * @return void
430  */
431 function drop(evt)
432 {
433 
434 	if(dragObj == null)
435 		return;
436 		
437 
438 
439 	switch(dragType)
440 	{
441 		case 'X':
442 			dragObj.setAttribute("x",getX(evt)-dragOffset);
443 			applet.dropX(dragObj.id);
444 			break;
445 		case 'Y':
446 			dragObj.setAttribute("y",getY(evt)-dragOffset);
447 			applet.dropY(dragObj.id);
448 			break;
449 		default: break;
450 	}
451 	dragObj =  null;
452 	dragOffset = 0;
453 	dragType = "";	
454 }
455 
456 /**
457  * Terminate a dragging operation.
458  * @param evt Event
459  * @return void
460  */
461 function endDrag(evt)
462 {
463 
464 	if(dragObj == null)
465 		return;
466 		
467 
468 	var el = evt.getTarget();
469 	dragObj =  null;
470 	dragOffset = 0;
471 	dragType = "";	
472 	
473 	if(applet != null)
474 		applet.endDrag();
475 }

477 /**
478  * @deprecated
479  * Delete a grille element.
480  * @param evt Event
481  * @return void
482  */
483 function deleteGrid(evt)
484 {
485 	if(dragObj == null)
486 		return;
487 	if(applet == null)
488 		return;
489 		
490 
491 
492 	switch(dragType)
493 	{
494 		case 'X':
495 			if(confirm("Delete " + dragObj.id + "?")==true)
496 			{
497 				applet.deleteX(dragObj.id);
498 			}
499 			break;
500 		case 'Y':
501 			if(confirm("Delete " + dragObj.id + "?")==true)
502 			{
503 				applet.deleteY(dragObj.id);
504 			}
505 			break;
506 		default: break;
507 	}
508 	dragObj =  null;
509 	dragOffset = 0;
510 	dragType = "";	
511 
512 }

514 /**
515  * Convert #'#-#/#" to decimal inches.
516  * @param dimension String
517  * @return decimal inches
518  */	
519 function dimToInches(dimension)
520 {
521 	if(trim(dimension) == "")
522 	{
523 		return 0;
524 	}
525 		
526 	var work = dimension+"";
527 	
528 	if(work.indexOf("\"") != -1)
529 	{
530 		work = dimension.replace("'","*12 + ");
531 		work = work.replace("-"," + ");
532 		work = work.replace("\"", "");
533 	}
534 	else
535 	{
536 		work = dimension.replace("'","*12");
537 	}
538 	try
539 	{
540 		var val = eval(work);
541 		if(val === undefined || isNaN(val))
542 		{
543 			return 0;
544 		}
545 		return val;
546 	}
547 	catch(x)
548 	{
549 		return 0;
550 	}
551 	
552 }
553 	
554 /**
555  * Convert feet,inches, fraction to decimal inches
556  * @param feet integer
557  * @param inches integer
558  * @param frac String fraction expression
559  * @return decimal inches
560  */		
561 function dimsToInches(feet, inches, frac)
562 {
563 	var result = 0;
564 	
565 	if(feet != "")
566 	{
567 		result += 12*(feet-0);
568 	}
569 	
570 	if(inches != "")
571 	{
572 		result += (inches-0);
573 	}
574 	
575 	if(frac != "")
576 	{
577 		try
578 		{
579 			var val = eval(frac);
580 			if(!(val === undefined || isNaN(val)))
581 				result+=val;
582 		}
583 		catch(x)
584 		{}
585 	}	
586 	return result;		
587 
588 }
589 	
590 /**
591  * Convert decimal inches to #'#-#/#" or if u/m is mm,
592  * return #mm.
593  * @param inches
594  * @return String dimension expression
595  */
596 function inchesToDim(inches)
597 {
598 	if(g("f_um") == "mm")
599 	{
600 		return inches+"mm";
601 	}
602 	
603 	var inchRemaining = inches%12;
604 	
605 	var feet = (inches - inchRemaining)/12;
606 	
607 	var fracRemaining = inchRemaining%1;
608 	var inchInteger = inchRemaining - fracRemaining;
609 	
610 	var frac = decToFraction(fracRemaining);
611 	
612 	var inch = "";
613 	
614 	if(inchInteger > 0 && frac != "")
615 	{
616 		inch = inchInteger + "-" + frac + "\"";
617 	}
618 	else
619 	{
620 		if(inchInteger > 0)
621 		{
622 			inch = inchInteger + "\"";
623 		}
624 		else
625 		{
626 		if(frac != "")
627 		{
628 			inch = frac + "\"";
629 		}
630 		else
631 		{
632 			inch = "0\"";
633 		}
634 		}
635 	}
636 	return trim((feet == 0?"":feet + "' ") + inch);
637 }
638 
639 /**
640  * Convert decimal inches to #-#/#
641  * @param inches
642  * @return
643  */
644 function inchesToInchesDim(inches)
645 {
646 	if(g("f_um") == "mm")
647 	{
648 		return inches+"mm";
649 	}
650 	var fracRemaining = inches%1;
651 	var inchInteger = inches - fracRemaining;
652 	
653 	var frac = decToFraction(fracRemaining);
654 	
655 	var inch = "";
656 	
657 	if(inchInteger > 0 && frac != "")
658 	{
659 		inch = inchInteger + "-" + frac + "\"";
660 	}
661 	else
662 	{
663 		if(inchInteger > 0)
664 		{
665 			inch = inchInteger + "\"";
666 		}
667 		else
668 		{
669 		if(frac != "")
670 		{
671 			inch = frac + "\"";
672 		}
673 		else
674 		{
675 			inch = "";
676 		}
677 		}
678 	}
679 	
680 	return trim(inch);
681 }
682 /**
683  * Convert a decimal to a fraction expression.
684  * @param indec
685  * @return String fraction expression (precision = 1/16)
686  */
687 function decToFraction(indec)
688 {
689 	var dec = indec % 1;
690 	if(dec == 0)
691 	{
692 		return "";
693 	}	
694 	var fracDec = 0;
695 	var fracs = ["0","1/16","1/8","3/16","1/4",   // TODO: support 1/32
696 					 "5/16","3/8","7/16","1/2",
697 					 "9/16","5/8","11/16","3/4",
698 					 "13/16","7/8","15/16","1"];
699 	var i = fracs.length - 1;
700 	for(; i >= 0; i--)
701 	{
702 		fracDec = eval(fracs[i]);
703 		if(fracDec <= dec)
704 		{
705 			return fracs[i];
706 		}
707 	}
708 	return "";
709 }
710 
711 /**
712  * Round a decimal number to the nearest 1/16th.
713  * @param inDec
714  * @return decimal
715  */	
716 function roundToSixteenth(inDec)
717 {
718 	var trimVal = inDec % .0625;
719 	return ((inDec - trimVal)*1000)/1000;
720 }

736 /**
737  * Radial point; x,y,c,a where c=circumference offset,a=angle in radians
738  * @constructor
739  * @param x decimal
740  * @param y decimal
741  * @param c decimal circumference offest from beginning of the arc
742  * @param a decimal angle(radians)
743  */
744 function RadialPoint(X,Y,C,A)
745 {
746 	this.x = X;
747 	this.y = Y;
748 	this.c = C;
749 	this.a = A;

752 /**
753  * Create a rectangular grille pattern
754  * 
755  * @param rectName String ID of containing glass pane
756  * @param gridElName String name of grille used as a prefix for naming
757  * 							the individual grille elements and punch point
758  * 							variables.
759  * @param pattern	String grille pattern code
760  * 							#V#H rectangular grid
761  * 							#H#V rectangular grid
762  * 							C#V#H craftsman grid
763  * 							D#V#H diamond grille
764  * 							P#T#B#L#R prairie
765  * @param color String webcolor
766  * @param t String thickness of grille element
767  * @return void
768  */
769 function initGrid(rectName,gridElName,patternParm,color,t)
770 {
771 trace("initGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+patternParm+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
772 try{
773 	var vert,horz,left,right,top,bottom;
774 	var pattern = new String(patternParm);
775 	switch(pattern.charAt(0))
776 	{
777 		case 'C': // Craftman
778 		//	vert = gN(gridElName+"v");
779 		//	if(vert == 0)
780 				s("f_"+gridElName+"v",pattern.charAt(1));
781 		//	horz =  gN(gridElName+"h");
782 		//	if(horz == 0)
783 				s("f_"+gridElName+"h",pattern.charAt(3));
784 		//	top = g(gridElName+"t");
785 		//	if(top == null)
786 				s("f_"+gridElName+"t",pattern.charAt(5));
787 			drawCraftsmanGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,false);
788 			break;	
789 
790 		case 'D': // Diamond
791 		//	vert = gN(gridElName+"v");
792 		//	if(vert == 0)
793 				s("f_"+gridElName+"v",pattern.charAt(1));
794 		//	horz =  gN(gridElName+"h");
795 		//	if(horz == 0)
796 				s("f_"+gridElName+"h",pattern.charAt(3));
797 			drawDiamondGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,false);
798 			break;	
799 		
800 	
801 		case 'P': // Prairie
802 		//	top = g(gridElName+"t");
803 		//	if(top == null)
804 				s("f_"+gridElName+"t",pattern.charAt(1));
805 		//	bottom = g(gridElName+"b");
806 		//	if(bottom == null)
807 				s("f_"+gridElName+"b",pattern.charAt(3));
808 		//	left = g(gridElName+"l");
809 		//	if(left == null)
810 				s("f_"+gridElName+"l",pattern.charAt(5));
811 		//	right = g(gridElName+"r");
812 		//	if(right == null)
813 				s("f_"+gridElName+"r",pattern.charAt(7));
814 			drawPrairieGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,false);
815 			break;	
816 		
817 		default:
818 		//	vert = gN(gridElName+"v");
819 		//	if(vert == 0)
820 				s("f_"+gridElName+"v",pattern.charAt(0));
821 		//	horz =  gN(gridElName+"h");
822 		//	if(horz == 0)
823 				s("f_"+gridElName+"h",pattern.charAt(2));
824 			drawGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,false);
825 			break;
826 	}
827 }catch(e)
828 {
829 	alertUser("Exception:  initGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+patternParm+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
830 	alertUser(e);
831 	trace(e);
832 }	
833 }
834 
835 /**
836  * @private
837  * Create a clippattern so any grille pattern can be superimposed
838  * over any shape window.  
839  * Caveat ... punch points cannot be calculated.
840  * 
841  * @param idGlass String id of glass pane
842  * @return void
843  */
844 function createClipPattern(idGlass)
845 {
846 
847  
848     var glass = drawing.getElementById(idGlass);
849     if(glass == null)
850     {
851          return;
852     }
853 
854 	var defsNodeList = drawing.getElementsByTagName("defs");
855     var defs = defsNodeList.item(0);
856     if(defs == null)
857     {
858          defs = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"defs");
859          drawing.getDocumentElement().appendChild(defs);
860     }
861  	var idPrefix = g("f_idprefix");
862      var clipPath = drawing.getElementById(idPrefix+"clip_"+idGlass);
863     if(clipPath == null)
864     {
865          clipPath = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"clipPath");
866          clipPath.setAttribute("id",idPrefix+"clip_"+idGlass);
867          defs.appendChild(clipPath);
868     }   
869     copyTree(clipPath,glass, idPrefix + "clip_dtl_");
870 
871 }
872 
873 /**
874  * Copy a DOM tree.
875  * 
876  * @param parent String ID target parent node
877  * @param source String ID source node
878  * @param idPrefix String modelset context prefix
879  * @return
880  */
881 function copyTree(parent,source,idPrefix)
882 {
883     var target = source.cloneNode(true);
884 
885     
886     target.setAttribute("id",idPrefix + source.getAttribute("id"));
887 
888     parent.appendChild(target);
889     
890 }

892 /**
893  * Draw a rectangular grid pattern.
894  * 
895  * @param rectName String id of glass pane
896  * @param gridElName String id and prefix for element names and punch
897  * 							point variables.
898  * @param color	String web color of grille
899  * @param t	Decimal thickness of grille element
900  * @param redraw boolean Is it a call to redraw the grid?
901  * @return void
902  */
903 function drawGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,redraw)
904 {
905 trace("drawGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
906 try{
907 var idPrefix = g("f_idprefix");
908 var redrawScript = 	"drawGrid('%ID%','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+",true)";
909 var	vert = gN("f_"+gridElName+"v");
910 var	horz = gN("f_"+gridElName+"h");
911 
912 createClipPattern(rectName);
913 	
914 	var rect = drawing.getElementById(rectName);
915 	if(rect == null)
916 	{
917 		trace("drawGrid() failed because " + rectName + " does not exist.");
918 		return;
919 	}
920 	
921 	
922 	var x = rect.getAttribute("x") - 0;
923 	var y = rect.getAttribute("y") - 0;
924 	var h = rect.getAttribute("height") - 0;
925 	var w = rect.getAttribute("width") - 0;
926 	if(applet && !redraw)
927 	{
928 			applet.registerLite(idPrefix+rectName,x+"",y+"",w+"",h+"",redrawScript);
929 			var elLite = drawing.getElementById(rectName);
930 			if(elLite != null)
931 			{
932 				elLite.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
933 				elLite.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
934 			}							 	
935 	}
936 	
937 
938 	var nVert = 1;
939 	var vSep = w/(vert+1);
940 	var window = drawing.getElementById("window");
941 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(gridElName);
942 	if(grp == null)
943 	{
944 		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
945 		grp.setAttribute("id",gridElName);
946 		grp.getStyle().setProperty("clip-path","url(#"+idPrefix+"clip_"+rectName+")","");
947 
948 		var ins = rect.nextSibling;
949 		if(ins == null)
950 		{
951 			window.appendChild(grp);
952 		}
953 		else
954 		{
955 			ins.parentNode.insertBefore(grp,ins);
956 		}
957 	}
958 
959 
960 	for(;nVert <= vert;nVert++)
961 	{
962 		var gvName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"v" + nVert;
963 		var gvVarName = gridElName+"v" + nVert;
964 		var gv = drawing.getElementById(gvName);
965 		var gvExists = true;
966 		if(gv == null)
967 		{
968 			gvExists = false;
969 			gv = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
970 			gv.setAttribute("id",gvName);
971 			gv.setAttribute("class","grid");
972 			gv.setAttribute("width",t);
973 			
974 			gv.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragX(evt)");							 	
975 			gv.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
976 			gv.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");	
977 	 		gv.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");
978 		}
979 		var t = gv.getAttribute("width")-0;
980 		var punchX =  g(gvVarName);
981 		if(punchX == null || punchX == 0)
982 		{
983 			punchX = (nVert*vSep);
984 		}
985 		punchX  = roundToSixteenth(punchX);
986 		gv.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
987 		
988 		gv.setAttribute("x",x + punchX - (t/2)); 
989 		gv.setAttribute("y",y);
990 		gv.setAttribute("height",h);
991 		if(!redraw && applet)
992 		{
993 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix+gvName,
994 										idPrefix+rectName,
995 										(x + punchX - (t/2)) +"", 	
996 										t + "",
997 										"s(\""+gvVarName+"\",%X%)");
998 			// return point
999 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix,
1000 										"",
1001 										(x + punchX - (t/2)) +"", 	
1002 										t + "",
1003 										null);
1004 										
1005 										
1006 		}
1007 		if(!gvExists)
1008 		{
1009 			grp.appendChild(gv);
1010 		}
1011 		var desc = "LENGTH: %H%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1012 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
1013 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchX));
1014 			
1015 		s(gvVarName,punchX);
1016 
1017 		createDescription(gvName,desc);
1018 			
1019 		
1020 	}
1021 
1022 	var nHorz = 1;
1023 	var hSep = h/(horz+1);
1024 	
1025 	for(;nHorz <= horz;nHorz++)
1026 	{	
1027 		var ghName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1028 		var ghVarName = gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1029 		var gh = drawing.getElementById(ghName);
1030 		var ghExists = true;
1031 		if(gh == null)
1032 		{
1033 			ghExists = false;
1034 			gh = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
1035 			gh.setAttribute("id",ghName);
1036 			gh.setAttribute("class","grid");
1037 			gh.setAttribute("height",t);
1038 			
1039 			gh.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragY(evt)");							 	
1040  			gh.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1041  			gh.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
1042 	 		gh.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");	
1043 		}
1044 		var t = gh.getAttribute("height")-0;
1045 	
1046 		var punchY =  g(ghVarName);
1047 
1048 		if(punchY == null || punchY == 0)
1049 		{
1050 			punchY = (hSep*nHorz);
1051 		}
1052 		punchY = roundToSixteenth(punchY);
1053 		
1054 		gh.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
1055 		gh.setAttribute("x",x); 
1056 		gh.setAttribute("y",y + punchY - (t/2));
1057 		gh.setAttribute("width",w);
1058 		
1059 		if(!redraw && applet)
1060 		{
1061 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix+ghName,
1062 										idPrefix+rectName,
1063 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1064 										t + "",
1065 										"s(\""+ghVarName+"\",%Y%)");
1066 			// return point
1067 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix,
1068 										"",
1069 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1070 										t + "",
1071 										null);
1072 		}
1073 		
1074 		if(!ghExists)
1075 		{
1076 			grp.appendChild(gh);
1077 		}
1078 		var desc = "LENGTH: %W%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1079 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
1080 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchY));
1081 		s(ghVarName,punchY);
1082 		createDescription(ghName,desc);
1083 	}
1084 }catch(e)
1085 {
1086 	alertUser("Exception:  drawGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
1087 	alertUser(e);
1088 	trace(e);
1089 }
1090 }

1108 /**
1109  * Draw horizontal grille bars
1110  * 
1111  * @param liteName  String id of containing lite
1112  * @param grp		String id of grille group (i.e. radial grille ID)
1113  * @param x			decimal x coordinate
1114  * @param y			decimal y coordinate
1115  * @param w			decimal width
1116  * @param h			decimal height
1117  * @param horz		integer bar count
1118  * @param color		String color code
1119  * @param t			decimal thickness of grille bar
1120  * @param startAtTop	boolean draw first bar at top (i.e. y)
1121  * @param redraw		boolean redrawing
1122  * @return void
1123  */
1124 
1125 
1126 function drawHorizontalBars(liteName,grp,x,y,w,h,horz,color,t,startAtTop,redraw)
1127 {
1128 trace("drawHorizontalBars('"+liteName+"','"+gridElName+"',"+x+","+y+","+w+","+h+","+horz+",'"+color+"',"+t+","+startAtTop+")");
1129 try{
1130 var idPrefix = g("f_idprefix");
1131 var redrawScript = 	"drawHorizontalBars('"+liteName+"','"+gridElName+"',"+x+","+y+","+w+","+h+","+horz+",'"+color+"',"+t+","+startAtTop+","+true+")";
1132 
1133 	
1134 	var nHorz = 1;
1135 	var hSep = startAtTop?h/(horz):h/(horz+1);
1136 	var ghName,ghVarName,gh,punchY,desc;
1137 	var gridElName = grp.getAttribute("id")+"_";
1138 	for(;nHorz <= horz;nHorz++)
1139 	{	
1140 		ghName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1141 		ghVarName = gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1142 		punchY =  g(ghVarName);
1143 
1144 		if(punchY == null || punchY == 0)
1145 		{
1146 			punchY = (hSep*(startAtTop?nHorz-1:nHorz));
1147 		}
1148 		punchY = roundToSixteenth(punchY);
1149 		
1150 		gh = drawing.getElementById(ghName);
1151 		if(gh === null)
1152 		{
1153 			gh = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
1154 			gh.setAttribute("id",ghName);
1155 			gh.setAttribute("class","grid");
1156 			gh.setAttribute("x",x); 
1157 			gh.setAttribute("y",y + punchY - (t/2));
1158 			gh.setAttribute("width",w);
1159 			gh.setAttribute("height",t);
1160 			
1161 			gh.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragY(evt)");							 	
1162  			gh.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1163  			gh.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
1164 	 		gh.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");	
1165 	 		grp.appendChild(gh);
1166 		}
1167 		
1168 		gh.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
1169 		gh.setAttribute("x",x); 
1170 		gh.setAttribute("y",y + punchY - (t/2));
1171 		gh.setAttribute("width",w);
1172 		gh.setAttribute("height",t);
1173 		
1174 		
1175 		if(!redraw && applet)
1176 		{
1177 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix+ghName,
1178 										idPrefix+liteName,
1179 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1180 										t + "",
1181 										"s(\""+ghVarName+"\",%Y%)");
1182 			// return point
1183 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix,
1184 										"",
1185 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1186 										t + "",
1187 										null);
1188 		}
1189 		
1190 		desc = "LENGTH: %W%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1191 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
1192 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchY));
1193 		s(ghVarName,punchY);
1194 		createDescription(ghName,desc);
1195 	}
1196 }catch(e)
1197 {
1198 	alertUser("Exception: drawHorizontalBars('"+liteName+"','"+gridElName+"',"+x+","+y+","+w+","+h+","+horz+",'"+color+"',"+t+","+startAtTop+")");
1199 
1200 	alertUser(e);
1201 	trace(e);
1202 }
1203 }

1225 /**

1227  * Requires caller to set these properties in the variable map:
1228  * 
1229  * s("f_"+gridElName+"v",<vertical bars>);
1230  * s("f_"+gridElName+"h", <horizonatal bars>);
1231  * s("f_"+gridElName+"t", <ladder count>);
1232  * 
1233  * @param rectName 		String id of containing glass pane
1234  * @param gridElName	String id of grid used as prefix of individual element IDs
1235  * @param color			String web color code

1238  * @return				void
1239  */
1240 
1241 
1242 function drawCraftsmanGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,redraw)
1243 {

1250 var	top = gN("f_"+gridElName+"t");  // ladder count
1251

1254 	if(rect == null)
1255 	{
1256 		trace("drawCraftsmanGrid() failed because " + rectName + " does not exist.");

1292 				if(ins == null)
1293 				{
1294 					window.appendChild(grp);
1295 				}
1296 				else
1297 				{
1298 					ins.parentNode.insertBefore(grp,ins);
1299 				}
1300 	}
1301 	
1302 	
1303 	for(;nVert <= vert;nVert++)

1345 										t + "",
1346 										null);
1347 										
1348 										
1349 		}
1350 		if(!gvExists)
1351 		{

1363 	}

1383  			gh.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
1384 	 		gh.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");	
1385 		}

1387 	
1388 		var punchY =  g(ghVarName);
1389 
1390 		if(punchY == null || punchY == 0)
1391 		{
1392 			punchY = (hSep*nHorz);
1393 		}

1399 		gh.setAttribute("width",w);
1400

1402 		{
1403 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix+ghName,
1404 										idPrefix+rectName,
1405 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1406 										t + "",
1407 										"s(\""+ghVarName+"\",%Y%)");
1408 			// return point

1410 										"",

1412 										t + "",
1413 										null);
1414 		}
1415

1417 		{
1418 			grp.appendChild(gh);
1419 		}

1421 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
1422 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchY));
1423 		s(ghVarName,punchY);
1424 		createDescription(ghName,desc);
1425 	}
1426 }catch(e)
1427 {
1428 	alertUser("Exception:  drawCraftsmanGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
1429 	alertUser(e);
1430 	trace(e);
1431 }
1432 }
1433 
1434 /**
1435  * Draw a prairie grid.
1436  * 
1437  * Requires caller to first set these values in the variable map:
1438  * s("f_"+gridElName+"l", <bars on left>);
1439  * s("f_"+gridElName+"r", <bars on right>);
1440  * s("f_"+gridElName+"t", <bars at top>);
1441  * s("f_"+gridElName+"b", <bars at bottom>);
1442  * s("f_"+gridElName+"sep", <separation of bars>);
1443  * 
1444  * 
1445  * @param rectName		String id of glass pane
1446  * @param gridElName	String id of grille and prefix of element IDs
1447  * @param color			String web color code
1448  * @param t				decimal thickness of elements
1449  * @param redraw		boolean redrawing
1450  * @return				void
1451  */
1452 
1453 function drawPrairieGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,redraw)
1454 {
1455 trace("drawGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
1456 try{
1457 var idPrefix = g("f_idprefix");
1458 var redrawScript = 	"drawGrid('%ID%','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+",true)";
1459 var	left = gN("f_"+gridElName+"l");
1460 var	right = gN("f_"+gridElName+"r");
1461 var	top = gN("f_"+gridElName+"t");
1462 var	bottom = gN("f_"+gridElName+"b");
1463 var sep = gN("f_"+gridElName+"sep");
1464 if(sep == 0)
1465 {
1466 	sep = gN("grid_sep");
1467 	if(sep == 0)
1468 		sep = 4;
1469 }
1470 var nVert = 0;
1471 var nHorz = 0;
1472 var desc,grp,ins, t,punchX,punchY;
1473 	
1474 	var rect = drawing.getElementById(rectName);
1475 	if(rect == null)
1476 	{
1477 		trace("drawGrid() failed because " + rectName + " does not exist.");
1478 		return;
1479 	}
1480 	
1481 	
1482 	var x = rect.getAttribute("x") - 0;
1483 	var y = rect.getAttribute("y") - 0;
1484 	var h = rect.getAttribute("height") - 0;
1485 	var w = rect.getAttribute("width") - 0;
1486 	if(applet && !redraw)
1487 	{
1488 			applet.registerLite(idPrefix+rectName,x+"",y+"",w+"",h+"",redrawScript);
1489 			var elLite = drawing.getElementById(rectName);
1490 			if(elLite != null)
1491 			{
1492 				elLite.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1493 				elLite.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
1494 			}							 	
1495 	}
1496 	
1497 
1498 	var nLeft = 1;
1499 	var window = drawing.getElementById("window");
1500 	createClipPattern(rectName);
1501 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(gridElName);
1502 	if(grp == null)
1503 	{
1504 				grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
1505 				grp.setAttribute("id",gridElName);
1506 				grp.getStyle().setProperty("clip-path","url(#"+idPrefix+"clip_"+rectName+")","");
1507 
1508 				var ins = rect.nextSibling;
1509 				if(ins == null)
1510 				{
1511 					window.appendChild(grp);
1512 				}
1513 				else
1514 				{
1515 					ins.parentNode.insertBefore(grp,ins);
1516 				}
1517 	}
1518 	
1519 	for(;nLeft <= left;nLeft++)
1520 	{
1521 		nVert++;
1522 		var glName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"v" + nVert;
1523 		var glVarName = gridElName+"v" + nVert;
1524 		var gl = drawing.getElementById(glName);
1525 		var glExists = true;
1526 		if(gl == null)
1527 		{
1528 			glExists = false;
1529 			gl = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
1530 			gl.setAttribute("id",glName);
1531 			gl.setAttribute("class","grid");
1532 			gl.setAttribute("width",t);
1533 			
1534 			gl.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragX(evt)");							 	
1535 			gl.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1536 			gl.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");	
1537 	 		gl.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");
1538 		}
1539 		punchX =  g(glVarName);
1540 		if(punchX == null || punchX == 0)
1541 		{
1542 			punchX = (nLeft*sep);
1543 		}
1544 		punchX  = roundToSixteenth(punchX);
1545 		gl.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
1546 		
1547 		gl.setAttribute("x",x + punchX - (t/2)); 
1548 		gl.setAttribute("y",y);
1549 		gl.setAttribute("height",h);
1550 		if(!redraw && applet)
1551 		{
1552 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix+glName,
1553 										idPrefix+rectName,
1554 										(x + (left*sep) - (t/2)) +"", 	
1555 										t + "",
1556 										"s(\""+glVarName+"\",%X%)");
1557 			// return point
1558 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix,
1559 										"",
1560 										(x + (nLeft*sep) - (t/2)) +"", 	
1561 										t + "",
1562 										null);
1563 										
1564 										
1565 		}
1566 		if(!glExists)
1567 		{
1568 			grp.appendChild(gl);
1569 		}
1570 		desc = "LENGTH: %H%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1571 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
1572 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchX));
1573 			
1574 		s(glVarName,punchX);
1575 
1576 		createDescription(glName,desc);
1577 	}
1578 
1579 
1580 	var nRight = 1;
1581 	for(;nRight <= right;nRight++)
1582 	{
1583 		nVert++;
1584 		var grName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"v" + nVert;
1585 		var grVarName = gridElName+"v" + nVert;
1586 		var gr = drawing.getElementById(grName);
1587 		var grExists = true;
1588 		if(gr == null)
1589 		{
1590 			grExists = false;
1591 			gr = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
1592 			gr.setAttribute("id",grName);
1593 			gr.setAttribute("class","grid");
1594 			gr.setAttribute("width",t);
1595 			
1596 			gr.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragX(evt)");							 	
1597 			gr.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1598 			gr.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");	
1599 	 		gr.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");
1600 		}
1601 		punchX =  g(grVarName);
1602 		if(punchX == null || punchX == 0)
1603 		{
1604 			punchX = w - (nRight*sep);
1605 		}
1606 		punchX  = roundToSixteenth(punchX);
1607 		gr.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
1608 		
1609 		gr.setAttribute("x",x + punchX); 
1610 		gr.setAttribute("y",y);
1611 		gr.setAttribute("height",h);
1612 		if(!redraw && applet)
1613 		{
1614 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix+grName,
1615 										idPrefix+rectName,
1616 										(x + punchX - (t/2)) +"", 	
1617 										t + "",
1618 										"s(\""+glVarName+"\",%X%)");
1619 			// return point
1620 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix,
1621 										"",
1622 										(x + punchX - (t/2)) +"", 	
1623 										t + "",
1624 										null);
1625 										
1626 										
1627 		}
1628 		if(!grExists)
1629 		{
1630 			grp.appendChild(gr);
1631 		}
1632 		desc = "LENGTH: %H%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1633 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
1634 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchX));
1635 			
1636 		s(grVarName,punchX);
1637 
1638 		createDescription(grName,desc);
1639 	}
1640 
1641 
1642 	var nTop = 1;
1643 	
1644 	for(;nTop <= top;nTop++)
1645 	{	
1646 		nHorz++;
1647 		var gtName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1648 		var gtVarName = gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1649 		var gt = drawing.getElementById(gtName);
1650 		var gtExists = true;
1651 		if(gt == null)
1652 		{
1653 			gtExists = false;
1654 			gt = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
1655 			gt.setAttribute("id",gtName);
1656 			gt.setAttribute("class","grid");
1657 			gt.setAttribute("height",t);
1658 			
1659 			gt.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragY(evt)");							 	
1660  			gt.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1661  			gt.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
1662 	 		gt.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");	
1663 		}
1664 		punchY =  g(gtVarName);
1665 
1666 		if(punchY == null || punchY == 0)
1667 		{
1668 			punchY = (sep*nTop);
1669 		}
1670 		punchY = roundToSixteenth(punchY);
1671 		
1672 		gt.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
1673 		gt.setAttribute("x",x); 
1674 		gt.setAttribute("y",y + punchY);
1675 		gt.setAttribute("width",w);
1676 		
1677 		if(!redraw && applet)
1678 		{
1679 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix+gtName,
1680 										idPrefix+rectName,
1681 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1682 										t + "",
1683 										"s(\""+gtVarName+"\",%Y%)");
1684 			// return point
1685 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix,
1686 										"",
1687 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1688 										t + "",
1689 										null);
1690 		}
1691 		
1692 		if(!gtExists)
1693 		{
1694 			grp = drawing.getElementById(gridElName);
1695 			if(grp == null)
1696 			{
1697 				grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
1698 				grp.setAttribute("id",gridElName);
1699 			
1700 				ins = rect.nextSibling;
1701 				if(ins == null)
1702 				{
1703 					window.appendChild(grp);
1704 				}
1705 				else
1706 				{
1707 					ins.parentNode.insertBefore(grp,ins);
1708 				}
1709 			}
1710 			grp.appendChild(gt);
1711 		}
1712 		desc = "LENGTH: %W%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1713 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
1714 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchY));
1715 		s(gtVarName,punchY);
1716 		createDescription(gtName,desc);
1717 	}
1718 	
1719 	var nBottom = 1;
1720 	
1721 	for(;nBottom <= bottom;nBottom++)
1722 	{	
1723 		nHorz++;
1724 		var gbName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1725 		var gbVarName = gridElName+"h"+nHorz;	
1726 		var gb = drawing.getElementById(gbName);
1727 		var gbExists = true;
1728 		if(gb == null)
1729 		{
1730 			gbExists = false;
1731 			gb = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
1732 			gb.setAttribute("id",gbName);
1733 			gb.setAttribute("class","grid");
1734 			gb.setAttribute("height",t);
1735 			
1736 			gb.setAttribute("onmousedown","startDragY(evt)");							 	
1737  			gb.setAttribute("onmousemove","drag(evt)");							 	
1738  			gb.setAttribute("onmouseup","drop(evt)");
1739 	 		gb.setAttribute("onmouseout","evt.stopPropagation()");	
1740 		}
1741 		punchY =  g(gbVarName);
1742 
1743 		if(punchY == null || punchY == 0)
1744 		{
1745 			punchY = h - (sep*nBottom);
1746 		}
1747 		punchY = roundToSixteenth(punchY);
1748 		
1749 		gb.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
1750 		gb.setAttribute("x",x); 
1751 		gb.setAttribute("y",y + punchY);
1752 		gb.setAttribute("width",w);
1753 		
1754 		if(!redraw && applet)
1755 		{
1756 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix+gbName,
1757 										idPrefix+rectName,
1758 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1759 										t + "",
1760 										"s(\""+gbVarName+"\",%Y%)");
1761 			// return point
1762 			applet.registerHorzElement( idPrefix,
1763 										"",
1764 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1765 										t + "",
1766 										null);
1767 		}
1768 		
1769 		if(!gbExists)
1770 		{
1771 			grp = drawing.getElementById(gridElName);
1772 			if(grp == null)
1773 			{
1774 				grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
1775 				grp.setAttribute("id",gridElName);
1776 			
1777 				ins = rect.nextSibling;
1778 				if(ins == null)
1779 				{
1780 					window.appendChild(grp);
1781 				}
1782 				else
1783 				{
1784 					ins.parentNode.insertBefore(grp,ins);
1785 				}
1786 			}
1787 			grp.appendChild(gb);
1788 		}
1789 		desc = "LENGTH: %W%  PUNCH: %P%.";
1790 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
1791 		desc = desc.replace(/%P%/g,inchesToInchesDim(punchY));
1792 		s(gbVarName,punchY);
1793 		createDescription(gbName,desc);
1794 	}
1795 }catch(e)
1796 {
1797 	alertUser("Exception:  drawPrairieGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
1798 	alertUser(e);
1799 	trace(e);
1800 }
1801 }

1803 
1804 /**
1805  * PRIVATE Create an element for a diamond grille pattern
1806  *   
1807  * @param gridElName 	String group id of grille 
1808  * @param n				integer 
1809  * @param color
1810  * @param t
1811  * @param grp
1812  * @param redraw
1813  * @return
1814  */
1815 function createDiamondPathElement(gridElName,n,color,t,grp,redraw)
1816 {
1817 	var gdName = (redraw?idPrefix:"")+gridElName+"d" + n;
1818 	var gd = drawing.getElementById(gdName);
1819 	var gdExists = true;
1820 	if(gd === null)
1821 	{
1822 		gdExists = false;
1823 //		gd = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"path");
1824 		gd = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"line");
1825 		gd.setAttribute("id",gdName);
1826 		gd.setAttribute("class","grid");
1827 		gd.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
1828 		gd.setAttribute("x1","0");
1829 		gd.setAttribute("y1","0");
1830 		gd.setAttribute("x2","1");
1831 		gd.setAttribute("y2","1");
1832 		gd.getStyle().setProperty("stroke",color,"");
1833 		gd.getStyle().setProperty("stroke-width",t,"");
1834 		
1835 		grp.appendChild(gd);
1836 		
1837 		createDescription(gdName," XXXXXXX");
1838 	}
1839 	return gd;
1840 }
1841 
1842 
1843 /**
1844  * Draw a diamond grille pattern.
1845  * 
1846  * Caller must first set the number vertical and horizonal lites
1847  * in the variable map:
1848  * s("f_"+gridElName+"v",<vertical lites>);
1849  * s("f_"+gridElName+"h",<horizontal lites>);
1850  * 
1851  * @param rectName		String id of glass pane
1852  * @param gridElName	String id and prefix of element IDs
1853  * @param color			String web color code
1854  * @param t				decimal element thickness
1855  * @param redraw		boolean redrawing
1856  * @return				void
1857  */
1858 
1859 function drawDiamondGrid(rectName,gridElName,color,t,redraw)
1860 {
1861 trace("drawDiamondGrid('"+ rectName+"','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+")");
1862 try{
1863 var idPrefix = g("f_idprefix");
1864 var redrawScript = 	"drawDiamondGrid('%ID%','"+gridElName+"','"+color+"',"+t+",true)";
1865 var	tb = gN("f_"+gridElName+"v");
1866 var	lr = gN("f_"+gridElName+"h");
1867 
1868 
1869 	var window = drawing.getElementById("window");
1870 	var rect = drawing.getElementById(rectName);
1871 	if(rect === null)
1872 	{
1873 		trace("drawDiamondGrid() failed because " + rectName + " does not exist.");
1874 		return;
1875 	}
1876 
1877 
1878 	createClipPattern(rectName);
1879 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(gridElName);
1880 	if(grp == null)
1881 	{
1882 				grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
1883 				grp.setAttribute("id",gridElName);
1884 				grp.getStyle().setProperty("clip-path","url(#"+idPrefix+"clip_"+rectName+")","");
1885 
1886 				var ins = rect.nextSibling;
1887 				if(ins == null)
1888 				{
1889 					window.appendChild(grp);
1890 				}
1891 				else
1892 				{
1893 					ins.parentNode.insertBefore(grp,ins);
1894 				}
1895 	}
1896 		
1897 	var x = rect.getAttribute("x") - 0;
1898 	var y = rect.getAttribute("y") - 0;
1899 	var h = rect.getAttribute("height") - 0;
1900 	var w = rect.getAttribute("width") - 0;
1901 	if(applet && !redraw)
1902 	{
1903 			applet.registerLite(idPrefix+rectName,x+"",y+"",w+"",h+"",redrawScript);
1904 	}
1905 
1906 	var nLR,nTB;
1907 	var hSep = w/lr;
1908 	var vSep = h/tb;
1909 	
1910 	// calculate the vertical (top/bottom) punch points
1911 	var nV = 1;
1912 	for(;nV < lr;nV++)
1913 	{
1914 		var gvVarName = gridElName+"v" + nV;
1915 		var punchX =  g(gvVarName);
1916 		if(punchX === null || punchX === 0)
1917 		{
1918 			punchX = (nV*hSep);
1919 		}
1920 		punchX  = roundToSixteenth(punchX);
1921 		s(gvVarName,punchX);
1922 		
1923 		if(!redraw && applet)
1924 		{
1925 			// alignment point
1926 			applet.registerVertElement(	idPrefix,
1927 										"",
1928 										(x + punchX - (t/2)) +"", 	
1929 										t + "",
1930 										null);
1931 						
1932 		}
1933 	}
1934 	
1935 	// calculate the horizontal (sides) punch points
1936 	var nH = 1;
1937 	for(;nH < tb;nH++)
1938 	{
1939 		var ghVarName = gridElName+"h" + nH;
1940 		var punchY =  g(ghVarName);
1941 		if(punchY === null || punchY === 0)
1942 		{
1943 			punchY = (nH*vSep);
1944 		}
1945 		punchY  = roundToSixteenth(punchY);
1946 		s(ghVarName,punchY);
1947 		
1948 		if(!redraw && applet)
1949 		{
1950 			// alignment point
1951 			applet.registerHorzElement(	idPrefix,
1952 										"",
1953 										(y + punchY - (t/2)) +"", 	
1954 										t + "",
1955 										null);
1956 						
1957 		}
1958 	}
1959 	
1960 	var gd,x1,y1,x2,y2,path,cornerX,cornerY,edgeX,edgeY;
1961 	var nD = 0;
1962 
1963 		cornerX = cornerY = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(t,2)/2);
1964 		edgeX = edgeY = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(t,2)*2);
1965 		
1966 		
1967 		if( lr == tb)
1968 		{
1969 			trace("lines from top to right");
1970 			for(nLR=0; nLR < lr; nLR++)
1971 			{ 
1972 				nD++;
1973 				gd = createDiamondPathElement(gridElName,nD,color,t,grp,redraw);
1974 				y1 = y;
1975 				x1 = x + (hSep*nLR);
1976 				x2 = x+w;
1977 				y2 = y + h - (vSep*(nLR-lr+tb));
1978 			
1979 				gd.setAttribute("x1",x1);
1980 				gd.setAttribute("y1",y1);
1981 				gd.setAttribute("x2",x2);
1982 				gd.setAttribute("y2",y2);
1983 			
1984 				trace(x1+","+y1+" --- "+x2+","+y2);
1985 			}
1986 
1987 			trace("lines from right to bottom");
1988 			for(nTB=0; nTB < tb; nTB++)
1989 			{    
1990 				nD++;
1991 				gd = createDiamondPathElement(gridElName,nD,color,t,grp,redraw);
1992 
1993 				x1 = x+w;
1994 				y1 = y+nTB*vSep;
1995 				x2 = x + nTB*hSep;
1996 				y2 = y+h;
1997 				
1998 				gd.setAttribute("x1",x1);
1999 				gd.setAttribute("y1",y1);
2000 				gd.setAttribute("x2",x2);
2001 				gd.setAttribute("y2",y2);
2002 				trace(x1+","+y1+" --- "+x2+","+y2);
2003 			
2004 			}
2005 			trace("lines from bottom to left");
2006 			for(nLR=1; nLR <= lr; nLR++)
2007 			{  
2008 				
2009 				nD++;
2010 				gd = createDiamondPathElement(gridElName,nD,color,t,grp,redraw);
2011 				x1 = (x+nLR*hSep);
2012 				y1 = y+h;
2013 				x2 = x;
2014 				y2 = y+h-(nLR*vSep);
2015 
2016 				gd.setAttribute("x1",x1);
2017 				gd.setAttribute("y1",y1);
2018 				gd.setAttribute("x2",x2);
2019 				gd.setAttribute("y2",y2);
2020

2245 /**
2246  * Create a direction indicator
2247  * 
2248  * @param id		String id
2249  * @param frame		String id of containing glass pane
2250  * @param direction	char direction code L,R,U,D
2251  * @return			void
2252  */
2253 function initDirection(id,frame,direction)
2254 {
2255 try{
2256 	trace("initDirection('"+id+"','"+frame+"','"+direction+"')");
2257 	var eFrame = drawing.getElementById(frame);
2258 	var xOffset = 0;
2259 	var yOffset = 0;
2260 	switch(direction)
2261 	{
2262 		case 'L': xOffset = -4; break;
2263 		case 'R': xOffset = 4; break;
2264 		case 'U': yOffset = -4; break;
2265 		case 'D': yOffset = 4; break;
2266 	}
2267 	
2268 	var dirX = 	getN(frame,"x") 
2269 				+ getN(frame,"width")/2
2270 				+ xOffset;
2271 	
2272 	var dirY = 	getN(frame,"y") 
2273 				+ getN(frame,"height")/2
2274 				+ yOffset;
2275 
2276 	var e = drawing.getElementById(id);
2277 	if(e == null)
2278 	{
2279 		e = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"path");
2280 		e.setAttribute("id",id);
2281 		e.setAttribute("class","direction");
2282 		e.setAttribute("d",drawDirection(direction,dirX,dirY));	
2283 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(e);
2284 	}
2285 	else
2286 	{
2287 		e.setAttribute("d",drawDirection(direction,dirX,dirY));	
2288 	}
2289 }catch(e)
2290 {
2291 	alertUser("Exception:  initDirection('"+id+"','"+frame+"','"+direction+"')");
2292 	alertUser(e);
2293 	trace(e);
2294 }	
2295 }
2296 
2297 /**
2298  * Draw a direction indicator
2299  * 
2300  * @param direction	char direction code L,R,U,D
2301  * @param x			decimal x coordinate
2302  * @param y			decimal y coordinate
2303  * @return			void
2304  */
2305 function drawDirection(direction,x,y)
2306 {
2307 
2308 	var path = "";
2309 	switch(direction)
2310 	{
2311 		case "D":
2312 			path = "M %X%,%Y% l 2.5,-2.5 l -5,0 l 2.5,2.5 m -2.5,-3.5 l 5,0 m -5,-1 l 5,0 m -5,-1 l 5,0";
2313 			break;
2314 		case "U":
2315 			path = "M %X%,%Y% l 2.5,2.5 l -5,0 l 2.5,-2.5 m -2.5,3.5 l 5,0 m -5,1 l 5,0 m -5,1 l 5,0";
2316 			break;
2317 		case "L":
2318 			path = "M %X%,%Y% l 5,-2.5 l 0,5 l -5,-2.5 m 6,-2.5 l 0,5 m 1,-5 l 0,5 m 1,-5 l 0,5";
2319 			break;
2320 		case "R":
2321 			path = "M %X%,%Y% l -5,-2.5 l 0,5 l 5,-2.5 m -6,-2.5 l 0,5 m -1,-5 l 0,5 m -1,-5 l 0,5";
2322 			break;
2323 	}
2324 	
2325 	path = path.replace(/%X%/g,x); 			
2326 	path = path.replace(/%Y%/g,y); 
2327 
2328 	return path;		
2329 }

2339 
2340 function initHanding(id,frame,handing)
2341 {

2399 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(e);
2400 	}
2401 	else
2402 	{
2403 		e.setAttribute("d",drawSwingDirection(frame,handing,frame_x,frame_y,frame_w,frame_h));
2404 	}

2413 
2414 /**
2415  * Draw the handing at specific coordinates.  
2416   * 
2417  * @param id		String id
2418  * @param handing	char handing direction (L,R,U,D)
2419  * @param frame_x	decimal x coordinate
2420  * @param frame_y	decimal y coordinate
2421  * @param frame_w	decimal width
2422  * @param frame_h	decimal height
2423  * @return			void
2424  */
2425 function drawSwingDirection(frame, handing,frame_x,frame_y,frame_w,frame_h)
2426 {
2427 	var handingPath = "";
2428 	var sx=0,sy=0,g1=0,g2=0,gm=0;
2429 	
2430 	switch(handing.charAt(0))
2431 	{
2432 		case 'U':
2433 			handingPath = "M %SX%,%SY% l %GM%,%G1% l %GM%,%G2%";
2434 			sx = frame_x + 3.75;
2435 			sy = frame_y + frame_h-3.75;
2436 			g1 = -(frame_h-7.5);
2437 			g2 = frame_h-7.5;
2438 			gm = (frame_w-7.5)/2;
2439 			break;
2440 		case 'D':
2441 			handingPath = "M %SX%,%SY% l %GM%,%G1% l %GM%,%G2%";
2442 			sx = frame_x + 3.75;
2443 			sy = frame_y + 3.75;
2444 			g1 = frame_h-7.5;
2445 			g2 = -(frame_h-7.5);
2446 			gm = (frame_w-7.5)/2;
2447 			break;
2448 		case 'L':
2449 			handingPath = "M %SX%,%SY% l %G1%,%GM% l %G2%,%GM%";
2450 			sx = frame_x + frame_w-3.75;
2451 			sy = frame_y + 3.75;
2452 			g1 = -(frame_w-7.5);
2453 			g2 = frame_w-7.5;
2454 			gm = (frame_h-7.5)/2;
2455 			break;
2456 		case 'R':
2457 			handingPath = "M %SX%,%SY% l %G1%,%GM% l %G2%,%GM%";
2458 			sx = frame_x + 3.75;
2459 			sy = frame_y + 3.75;
2460 			g1 = frame_w-7.5;
2461 			g2 = -(frame_w-7.5);
2462 			gm = (frame_h-7.5)/2;
2463 			break;	
2464 	}
2465 	handingPath=handingPath.replace(/%SX%/g,sx);
2466 	handingPath=handingPath.replace(/%SY%/g,sy);
2467 	handingPath=handingPath.replace(/%G1%/g,g1);
2468 	handingPath=handingPath.replace(/%G2%/g,g2);
2469 	handingPath=handingPath.replace(/%GM%/g,gm);
2470 
2471 	return handingPath;
2472 }

2623 /**

2625  *

2627  * @return	String
2628  */
2629 function getText(entity)
2630 {
2631 try{
2632 	trace("getText('"+entity+"')");
2633 
2634 	var e = drawing.getElementById(entity);
2635 	if(e != null)
2636 	{
2637 		if(e.firstChild)
2638 		{
2639 			return	e.firstChild.nodeValue;
2640 		}
2641 	}
2642 	return "";
2643 }	
2644 catch(e)
2645 {
2646 	alertUser("Exception:  getText('"+entity+"')");
2647 	alertUser(e);
2648 	trace(e);
2649 }

2652 /**
2653  * Convert from drawing units to pixels
2654  * 
2655  * @param drawingUnits	decimal
2656  * @return	decimal	pixels
2657  */
2658 function toPixels(drawingUnits)
2659 {
2660    var SVGRoot = drawing.getDocumentElement();
2661    var m = SVGRoot.getScreenCTM(); 
2662    var p = SVGRoot.createSVGPoint(); 
2663    p.x = drawingUnits; 
2664    p.y = drawingUnits; 
2665    p = p.matrixTransform();
2666    return p.x; 
2667 }
2668 
2669 
2670 /**
2671  * Convert from pixels to drawing units
2672  * 
2673  * @param z		decimal pixels
2674  * @return	decimal drawing units
2675  */
2676 function toDrawingUnits(z)
2677 {
2678             var SVGRoot = drawing.getDocumentElement();
2679             var m = SVGRoot.getScreenCTM(); 
2680             var p = SVGRoot.createSVGPoint(); 
2681             p.x = z; 
2682             p.y = z; 
2683             p = p.matrixTransform(m.inverse());
2684 	         return p.x; 
2685 }

2687 /**
2688  * Get the point of a mouse event in drawing units.
2689  * 
2690  * @param evt	Event object
2691  * @return	Point
2692  */
2693 function getPoint(evt)
2694 {
2695             var SVGRoot = drawing.getDocumentElement();
2696             var m = SVGRoot.getScreenCTM(); 
2697             var p = SVGRoot.createSVGPoint(); 
2698             p.x = evt.clientX; 
2699             p.y = evt.clientY; 
2700             p = p.matrixTransform(m.inverse());
2701 	         return p; 
2702 }
2703 
2704 /**
2705  * Get x coordinate of a mouse event in drawing units.
2706  * 
2707  * @param evt	Event
2708  * @return decimal 
2709  */
2710 function getX(evt)
2711 {
2712 	return	getPoint(evt).x;
2713 }
2714 
2715 /**
2716  * Get y coordinate of a mouse event in drawing units.
2717  * 
2718  * @param evt	Event
2719  * @return decimal 
2720  */
2721 function getY(evt)
2722 {
2723 	return getPoint(evt).y;
2724 }

2731  * @return

2739 	}

2742 /**
2743  * Create a rectangular glass pane.
2744  * 
2745  * @param id		String id 
2746  * @param sashId	String id of containing sash/frame
2747  * @param x			decimal x
2748  * @param y			decimal y
2749  * @param w			decimal width
2750  * @param h			decimal height
2751  * @param v			decimal invisible inset 
2752  * @return
2753  */
2754 
2755 function initGlass(id,sashId,x, y, w, h, v)
2756 {
2757 try
2758 {
2759 trace("initGlass('"+id+"','"+sashId+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ v+")");
2760 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(id);
2761 	var idPrefix = g("f_idprefix");
2762 	if(grp == null)
2763 	{
2764 		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
2765 		grp.setAttribute("id",id);
2766 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(grp);
2767 	}
2768 	
2769 	var gls = drawing.getElementById(id+"_pane");
2770 	var gExists = gls != null;
2771 	if(!gExists)
2772 	{
2773 		
2774 		gls = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
2775 		gls.setAttribute("id",id+"_pane");
2776 		gls.setAttribute("class","glass")
2777 		gls.setAttribute("onmouseover","expose(evt,'"+idPrefix+sashId+"',true)");
2778 		gls.setAttribute("onmouseout","expose(evt,'"+idPrefix+sashId+"',false)");
2779 	}
2780 
2781 	gls.setAttribute("x",x);
2782 	gls.setAttribute("y",y);
2783 	gls.setAttribute("width",w);
2784 	gls.setAttribute("height",h);
2785 	if(!gExists)
2786 	{
2787 		grp.appendChild(gls);
2788 	}
2789 	var t,tText;
2790 	if(g("f_glass") == "TEMPERED")
2791 	{
2792 	trace("creating T");
2793 		t = drawing.getElementById(id+"_pane_t");
2794 		if(t == null)
2795 		{
2796 			t = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"text");
2797 			t.setAttribute("id",id+"_pane_t");
2798 			t.setAttribute("class","glass");
2799    			tText = drawing.createTextNode("T");
2800     		t.appendChild(tText);
2801 			grp.appendChild(t);			
2802 		}
2803 		t.setAttribute("x",x+w-2);
2804 		t.setAttribute("y",y+h-2);
2805 	}
2806 	
2807 
2808 	if(g("f_tn")!="true")
2809 	{
2810 		var desc = "WIDTH: %W%  HEIGHT: %H%  VISIBLE: %WV%X%HV%.";
2811 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
2812 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
2813 		desc = desc.replace(/%WV%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w-(2*v)));
2814 		desc = desc.replace(/%HV%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h-(2*v)));
2815 		createDescription(id+"_pane",desc);
2816 	}
2817 }	
2818 catch(e)
2819 {
2820 	alertUser("Exception:  initGlass('"+id+"','"+sashId+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ v+")");
2821 	alertUser(e);
2822 	trace(e);
2823 }	
2824 }

2827 /**
2828  * Draw a rectangle.
2829  * 
2830  * @param id		String id
2831  * @param x			decimal x
2832  * @param y			decimal y
2833  * @param w			decimal width
2834  * @param h			decimal height
2835  * @param color		String web color code
2836  * @return
2837  */
2838 function initRect(id, x, y, w, h, color)
2839 {
2840 try
2841 {
2842 trace("initRect('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+",'"+ color+"')");
2843 	var fillH = color.charAt(0) == '*' ? "url(#"+ g(color.substring(1))+"H)" : color;
2844 	var fillV = color.charAt(0) == '*' ? "url(#"+ g(color.substring(1))+"V)" : color;
2845 trace("fillH="+fillH);
2846 trace("fillV="+fillV);
2847 
2848 	var e = drawing.getElementById(id);
2849 	if(e===null)
2850 	{
2851 		e = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
2852 		e.setAttribute("id",id);
2853 		e.setAttribute("x",x);
2854 		e.setAttribute("y",y);
2855 		e.setAttribute("width",w);
2856 		e.setAttribute("height",h);
2857 		e.setAttribute("class","frame");
2858 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(e);
2859 	}
2860 	e.setAttribute("x",x);
2861 	e.setAttribute("y",y);
2862 	e.setAttribute("width",w);
2863 	e.setAttribute("height",h);
2864 	if(color !== null)
2865 	{
2866 		e.getStyle().setProperty("fill",w>h?fillH:fillV,"");
2867 	}
2868 	if(g("f_tn")== "true")
2869 	{
2870 		e.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
2871 	}
2872 	else
2873 	{
2874 		var desc = "WIDTH: " + inchesToInchesDim(w) + " HEIGHT: " + inchesToInchesDim(h) + ".";
2875 		createDescription(id,desc);
2876 	}
2877 }	
2878 catch(e)
2879 {
2880 	alertUser("Exception:  initRect('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+",'"+ color+"')");
2881 	alertUser(e);
2882 	trace(e);
2883 }	
2884 }

3254 	path=path.replace(/%HL%/g,h);
3255 	path=path.replace(/%HS%/g,hs);
3256 	path=path.replace(/%FS%/g,fSide);
3257 	left.setAttribute("d",path);
3258 	left.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
3259 	if(tn)
3260 	{
3261 		left.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
3262 	}
3263 	else
3264 	{
3265 		desc = "LENGTH: %H% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3266 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
3267 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(fSide));
3268 		createDescription(id+"_left",desc);
3269 	}
3270 	
3271 	// right
3272 	var right = drawing.getElementById(id+"_right");
3273 	if(right == null)
3274 	{
3275 		right = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS, "path");
3276 		right.setAttribute("id",id+"_right");
3277 		right.setAttribute("class","frame");
3278 		
3279 		grp.appendChild(right);
3280 	}
3281 	path = "M %X%,%Y% l 0,%HL% l -%FS%,0 l 0,-%HS% L %X%,%Y%";
3282 	path=path.replace(/%X%/g,x+w);
3283 	path=path.replace(/%Y%/g,y);
3284 	path=path.replace(/%HL%/g,h);
3285 	path=path.replace(/%HS%/g,hs);
3286 	path=path.replace(/%FS%/g,fSide);
3287 	right.setAttribute("d",path);
3288 	right.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
3289 	if(tn)
3290 	{
3291 		right.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
3292 	}
3293 	else
3294 	{
3295 		desc = "LENGTH: %H%  ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3296 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
3297 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(fSide));
3298 		createDescription(id+"_right",desc);
3299 	
3300 		desc = "WIDTH: %W% HEIGHT: %H%.";
3301 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
3302 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
3303 
3304 		createDescription(id,desc);
3305 	//	grp.setAttribute("onmousedown","showDescription(evt,true)");
3306 	//	grp.setAttribute("onmouseup","showDescription(evt,false)");
3307 	}
3308 }	
3309 catch(e)
3310 {
3311 	alertUser("Exception:  initDoorNoThresholdMitredFrame('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ fTop+","+fSide+",'"+ color+"')");

3317 /**
3318  * Associate a title to a drawing element.
3319  *  
3320  * @param subjectID		String id
3321  * @param text			String text
3322  * @return	void
3323  */
3324 function createDescription(subjectID, text)
3325 {
3326 	if(g("f_applet")!="true")
3327 	{
3328 		return;
3329 	}
3330 	
3331 	var subject = drawing.getElementById(subjectID);
3332 	if(subject == null)
3333 	{
3334 		alert("createDescription():  subject -" + subjectID + "- does not exist.");
3335 		return;
3336 	}
3337 
3338     var e = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS ,"title");
3339

3341

3345 		return;
3346 	}

3348     e.appendChild(textContent);
3349 	subject.appendChild(e);

3353 /**
3354  * Create a dimension.
3355  * 
3356  * @param x1		decimal x1
3357  * @param y1		decimal y1
3358  * @param x2		decimal x2
3359  * @param y2		decimal y2
3360  * @param showFeet	boolean display feet (true) or just inches (false)
3361  * @return	void
3362  */ 
3363 
3364 function createDim(x1,y1,x2,y2,showFeet)
3365 {
3366 try{
3367 trace("createDim("+x1+","+y1+","+x2+","+y2+","+showFeet+")");
3368 var um = g("f_um");
3369 if(um === null)
3370 {
3371 	um = "in";
3372 }
3373 	if(g("f_tn")=="true")
3374 	{
3375 		return;
3376 	}
3377 	var length = Math.sqrt(Math.pow(x2-x1,2)+Math.pow(y2-y1,2));
3378 	
3379 	if((x1 > x2) || (x1 == x2 && y2 < y1))
3380 	{ // flip it so the arrows don't get reversed.
3381 		var x = x1;
3382 		x1 = x2;
3383 		x2 = x;
3384 		var y = y1;
3385 		y1 = y2;
3386 		y2 = y;
3387 	}
3388 
3389 	// showFeet = false;
3390 
3391 	var rotate = 0;
3392 	if(x1 == x2)
3393 	{
3394 		rotate = 90;
3395 	}
3396 	else
3397 	{
3398 		if(y1 == y2)
3399 		{
3400 			rotate = 0;
3401 		}
3402 		else
3403 		{
3404 			rotate = Math.round((Math.atan((y2-y1)/(x2-x1)))*180);  //TODO: this doesn't work!
3405 		}
3406 	}
3407 	var rotateRev = rotate + 180;
3408 
3409 	
3410 	var l = Math.sqrt(((x2-x1)*(x2-x1)) + ((y2-y1)*(y2-y1)));
3411 	var dimText = null;
3412 	
3413 	if(um == "mm")
3414 	{
3415 		dimText = l + "mm";
3416 	}
3417 	else
3418 	{
3419 		dimText = showFeet ? inchesToDim(l):inchesToInchesDim(l);
3420 	}
3421 
3422    	var grp = drawing.getElementById("f_dims");
3423    	if(grp == null)
3424    	{
3425    		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
3426    		grp.setAttribute("id","f_dims");
3427    	}
3428    	
3429    	var xC = x1 + (x2-x1)/2;
3430   	var yC = y1 + (y2-y1)/2;
3431 /*
3432  alert("rotate="+rotate
3433  	+ " rotateRev=" + rotateRev
3434 	+ " x1=" + x1
3435 	+ " y1=" + y1
3436 	+ " xC=" + xC
3437 	+ " yC=" + yC
3438 	+ " x2=" + x2
3439  	+ " y2=" + y2
3440  	+ " dimText=" + dimText);
3441 */ 	
3442  
3443 
3444 if(length < 8)
3445 {
3446 var line1 = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"line");
3447 var line2 = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"line");
3448 	if(rotate == 0)
3449 	{
3450    		line1.setAttribute("x1",x1);
3451   		line1.setAttribute("x2",x1);
3452   		line1.setAttribute("y1",y1-1);
3453  		line1.setAttribute("y2",y1+1);
3454  		line2.setAttribute("x1",x2);
3455   		line2.setAttribute("x2",x2);
3456   		line2.setAttribute("y1",y2-1);
3457  		line2.setAttribute("y2",y2+1);
3458  	}
3459  	else
3460  	{
3461    		line1.setAttribute("x1",x1-1);
3462   		line1.setAttribute("x2",x1+1);
3463   		line1.setAttribute("y1",y1);
3464  		line1.setAttribute("y2",y1);
3465  		line2.setAttribute("x1",x2-1);
3466   		line2.setAttribute("x2",x2+1);
3467   		line2.setAttribute("y1",y2);
3468  		line2.setAttribute("y2",y2);
3469  	}	
3470  	line1.setAttribute("class","dimEnd");
3471   	grp.appendChild(line1);
3472 	line2.setAttribute("class","dimEnd");
3473   	grp.appendChild(line2);
3474  }
3475 else
3476 {
3477 // create faint dashed line
3478     var line = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"line");
3479    	line.setAttribute("x1",x1);
3480   	line.setAttribute("x2",x2);
3481   	line.setAttribute("y1",y1);
3482   	line.setAttribute("y2",y2);
3483   	line.setAttribute("class","dim");
3484 
3485   	grp.appendChild(line);
3486 // create starting arrow  	
3487    	var g1= drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
3488    	g1.setAttribute("transform","translate("+x1+","+y1+")");
3489 	var g2 = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");  
3490   	g2.setAttribute("transform","rotate("+rotate+")");
3491 	var use = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"use");
3492 	use.setAttributeNS(xlinkNS,"href","#arrow");
3493 	g2.appendChild(use);
3494 	g1.appendChild(g2);
3495 	grp.appendChild(g1);
3496 	
3497 // create ending arrow	
3498 	g1= drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
3499    	g1.setAttribute("transform","translate("+x2+","+y2+")");
3500 	g2 = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");  
3501   	g2.setAttribute("transform","rotate("+rotateRev+")");
3502 	use = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"use");
3503 	use.setAttribute("xlink:href","#arrow");
3504 	use.setAttributeNS(xlinkNS,"href","#arrow");
3505 	g2.appendChild(use);
3506 	g1.appendChild(g2);
3507 	grp.appendChild(g1);
3508 }
3509 
3510 // create text caption
3511 	g1= drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
3512 	if(rotate<0)
3513 	{
3514 		rotate+=180;
3515    	}
3516    	g1.setAttribute("transform","rotate("+rotate+","+xC+","+(yC)+")");
3517 	var text = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"text");
3518 	text.setAttribute("x",xC);
3519 	text.setAttribute("y",(yC+1));
3520 	text.setAttribute("class",length<8?"dimSmall":"dim");
3521 	var textContent = drawing.createTextNode(dimText);
3522 	text.appendChild(textContent);
3523 	g1.appendChild(text);
3524 	grp.appendChild(g1);
3525 	
3526 	drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(grp);
3527 }	
3528 catch(e)
3529 {
3530 	alertUser("Exception:  createDim("+x1+","+y1+","+x2+","+y2+","+showFeet+")");
3531 	alertUser(e);
3532 	trace(e);
3533 }
3534 }

3538 /**
3539  * Draw a mitred frame where the sides, the top, and the bottom
3540  * frame thickness can all vary.
3541  * 
3542  * @param id		String id
3543  * @param x			decimal x coordinate
3544  * @param y			decimal y coordinate
3545  * @param w			decimal width
3546  * @param h			decimal height
3547  * @param f			decimal side frame thickness
3548  * @param fTop		decimal top frame thickness
3549  * @param fBot		decimal bottom frame thickness
3550  * @param color		String web color code
3551  * @return
3552  */
3553 
3554 function initOuterMiterFrame(id, x, y, w, h, f,fTop,fBot, color)
3555 {
3556 try
3557 {
3558 trace("initOuterMiterFrame('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ f+","+ fTop+","+ fBot+",'"+ color+"')");
3559 
3560 	var ws = w - (2*f);
3561 	var hs = h - fTop - fBot;
3562 	var desc = "";
3563 	var tn = g("f_tn") == "true";
3564 
3565 
3566 	// frame group
3567 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(id);
3568 	if(grp === null)
3569 	{
3570 		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
3571 		grp.setAttribute("id",id);
3572 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(grp);
3573 	}
3574 	// top
3575 	var top = drawing.getElementById(id+"_header");
3576 	if(top === null)
3577 	{
3578 		top = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"path");
3579 		top.setAttribute("id",id+"_header");
3580 		top.setAttribute("class","frame");
3581 		top.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
3582 		grp.appendChild(top);
3583 	}
3584 	var path = "M "+x+","+y+" l "+w+",0 ";
3585 	if(fTop <= f)
3586 	{
3587 		path += "l -"+fTop+","+fTop+ " l -"+(w-(fTop*2))+",0 l -"+fTop+",-"+fTop;
3588 	}
3589 	else
3590 	if(fTop > f)
3591 	{
3592 			path += "l -"+f+","+f+ " l 0,"+(fTop-f)+" l -"+(w-(f*2))+",0 l 0,-"+(fTop-f)+" l -"+f+",-"+f;
3593 	}
3594 	top.setAttribute("d",path);
3595 	top.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
3596 	if(tn)
3597 	{
3598 		top.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
3599 	}
3600 	else
3601 	{	
3602 		desc = "LENGTH: %W% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3603 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
3604 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(fTop));
3605 		createDescription(id+"_header",desc);
3606 	}
3607 	
3608 	// bottom
3609 	var bot = drawing.getElementById(id+"_sill");
3610 	if(bot === null)
3611 	{
3612 		bot = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS ,"path");
3613 		bot.setAttribute("id",id+"_sill");
3614 		bot.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
3615 		bot.setAttribute("class","frame");
3616 		
3617 		grp.appendChild(bot);
3618 	}
3619 	path = "M "+x+","+(y+h)+" l "+w+",0 ";
3620 	if(fBot <= f)
3621 	{
3622 		path += "l -"+fBot+",-"+fBot+ " l -"+(w-(fBot*2))+",0 l -"+fBot+","+fBot;
3623 	}
3624 	else
3625 	if(fBot > f)
3626 	{
3627 			path += "l -"+f+",-"+f+ " l 0,-"+(fBot-f)+" l -"+(w-(f*2))+",0 l 0,"+(fBot-f)+" l -"+f+","+f;
3628 	}
3629 	bot.setAttribute("d",path);
3630 	bot.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
3631 	if(tn)
3632 	{
3633 		bot.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
3634 	}
3635 	else
3636 	{
3637 		desc = "LENGTH: %W% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3638 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
3639 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(fBot));
3640 		createDescription(id+"_sill",desc);
3641 	}
3642 	
3643 	// left
3644 	var left = drawing.getElementById(id+"_left_jamb");
3645 	if(left === null)
3646 	{
3647 		left = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"path");
3648 		left.setAttribute("id",id+"_left_jamb");
3649 		left.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
3650 		left.setAttribute("class","frame");
3651 		
3652 		grp.appendChild(left);
3653 	}
3654 	
3655 	path = "M "+x+","+(y)+" l 0,"+h;
3656 	if(fBot >= f)
3657 	{
3658 		path += " l "+f+",-"+f;
3659 	}
3660 	else
3661 	if(fBot < f)
3662 	{
3663 		path += " l "+fBot+",-"+fBot + " l "+(f - fBot)+",0 ";
3664 	}
3665 	if(fTop >= f)
3666 	{
3667 		path += " l 0,-"+(h-f-Math.min(fBot,f))+" l -"+f+",-"+f;
3668 	}
3669 	else
3670 	if(fTop < f)
3671 	{
3672 		path += " l 0,-"+(h-fTop-Math.min(fBot,f))+" l -"+(f-fTop)+",0 l -"+fTop+",-"+fTop;
3673 	}
3674 	left.setAttribute("d",path);
3675 	left.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
3676 	if(tn)
3677 	{
3678 		left.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
3679 	}
3680 	else
3681 	{
3682 		desc = "LENGTH: %H% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3683 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
3684 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(f));
3685 		createDescription(id+"_left_jamb",desc);
3686 	}
3687 	
3688 	// right
3689 	var right = drawing.getElementById(id+"_right_jamb");
3690 	if(right === null)
3691 	{
3692 		right = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS, "path");
3693 		right.setAttribute("id",id+"_right_jamb");
3694 		right.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
3695 		right.setAttribute("class","frame");
3696 		
3697 		grp.appendChild(right);
3698 	}
3699 	path = "M "+(x+w)+","+(y)+" l 0,"+h;
3700 	if(fBot >= f)
3701 	{
3702 		path += " l -"+f+",-"+f;
3703 	}
3704 	else
3705 	if(fBot < f)
3706 	{
3707 		path += " l -"+fBot+",-"+fBot + " l -"+(f - fBot)+",0 ";
3708 	}
3709 	if(fTop >= f)
3710 	{
3711 		path += " l 0,-"+(h-f-Math.min(fBot,f))+" l "+f+",-"+f;
3712 	}
3713 	else
3714 	if(fTop < f)
3715 	{
3716 		path += " l 0,-"+(h-fTop-Math.min(fBot,f))+" l "+(f-fTop)+",0 l "+fTop+",-"+fTop;
3717 	}
3718 	right.setAttribute("d",path);
3719 	right.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
3720 	if(tn)
3721 	{
3722 		right.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
3723 	}
3724 	else
3725 	{
3726 		desc = "LENGTH: %H%  ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3727 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
3728 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(f));
3729 		createDescription(id+"_right_jamb",desc);
3730 	
3731 		desc = "WIDTH: %W% HEIGHT: %H% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
3732 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
3733 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
3734 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(f));
3735 
3736 		createDescription(id,desc);
3737 	}
3738 }	
3739 catch(e)
3740 {
3741 	alertUser("Exception:  initOuterMiterFrame('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ f+","+ fTop+","+ fBot+",'"+ color+"')");

3939 /**
3940  * Draw a shutter frame where the sides, the top, and the bottom
3941  * frame thickness can all vary.
3942  * 
3943  * @param id		String id
3944  * @param x			decimal x coordinate
3945  * @param y			decimal y coordinate
3946  * @param w			decimal width
3947  * @param h			decimal height
3948  * @param f			decimal side frame thickness
3949  * @param fTop		decimal top frame thickness
3950  * @param fBot		decimal bottom frame thickness
3951  * @param color		String web color code or SPECIES code for wood grain
3952  * @return
3953  */
3954 function initShutterFrame(id, x, y, w, h, f,fTop,fBot, color)
3955 {
3956 try
3957 {
3958 trace("initShutterFrame('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ f+","+fTop+","+ fBot+",'"+ color+"')");
3959 
3960 	var ws = w - (2*f);
3961 	var hs = h - fBot;
3962 	var desc = "";
3963 	var tn = g("f_tn") == "true";
3964 
3965 	var fillH = color.charAt(0) == '*' ? "url(#"+ g(color.substring(1))+"H)" : color;
3966 	var fillV = color.charAt(0) == '*' ? "url(#"+ g(color.substring(1))+"V)" : color;
3967 	// frame group
3968 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(id);
3969 	if(grp === null)
3970 	{
3971 		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
3972 		grp.setAttribute("id",id);
3973 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(grp);
3974 	}
3975 	// top
3976 	var top = drawing.getElementById(id+"_header");
3977 	if(top === null)
3978 	{
3979 		top = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"rect");
3980 		top.setAttribute("id",id+"_header");
3981 		top.setAttribute("class","frame");
3982 		top.setAttribute("x",x+f);
3983 		top.setAttribute("y",y);
3984 		top.setAttribute("width",ws);
3985 		top.setAttribute("height",fTop);
3986 		top.getStyle().setProperty("fill",fillH,"");
3987 		grp.appendChild(top);
3988 	}
3989 	else
3990 	{
3991 		top.setAttribute("x",x+f);
3992 		top.setAttribute("y",y);
3993 		top.setAttribute("width",ws);
3994 		top.setAttribute("height",fTop);
3995 		top.getStyle().setProperty("fill",fillH,"");
3996 	}
3997 	if(tn)
3998 	{
3999 		top.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
4000 	}
4001 	else
4002 	{	
4003 				desc = "LENGTH: %W% ... %F% basswood stock.";
4004 				desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(ws));
4005 				desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(fTop));
4006 				createDescription(id+"_header",desc);
4007 	}
4008 
4009 	// bottom
4010 	var bot = drawing.getElementById(id+"_sill");
4011 	if(bot === null)
4012 	{
4013 		bot = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS ,"rect");
4014 		bot.setAttribute("id",id+"_sill");
4015 		bot.setAttribute("class","frame");

4129 /**
4130  * Draw a mitred door frame.
4131  * 
4132  * @param id		String id
4133  * @param x			decimal x coordinate
4134  * @param y			decimal y coordinate
4135  * @param w			decimal width
4136  * @param h			decimal height
4137  * @param f			decimal side frame thickness
4138  * @param color		String web color code
4139  * @return
4140  */
4141 function initDoorMiterFrame(id, x, y, w, h, f, color)
4142 {
4143 try
4144 {
4145 trace("initMitredFrame('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ f+",'"+ color+"')");
4146 
4147 	var ws = w - (2*f);
4148 	var hs = h - (2*f);
4149 	var desc = "";
4150 	var tn = g("f_tn") == "true";
4151 
4152 
4153 	// frame group
4154 	var grp = drawing.getElementById(id);
4155 	if(grp == null)
4156 	{
4157 		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
4158 		grp.setAttribute("id",id);
4159 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(grp);
4160 	}
4161 	// top
4162 	var top = drawing.getElementById(id+"_header");
4163 	if(top == null)
4164 	{
4165 		top = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"path");
4166 		top.setAttribute("id",id+"_header");
4167 		top.setAttribute("class","frame");
4168 		top.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
4169 		grp.appendChild(top);
4170 	
4171 		var path = "M %X%,%Y% l %WL%,0 l -%F%,%F% l -%WS%,0 l -%F%,-%F%";
4172 		path=path.replace(/%X%/g,x);
4173 		path=path.replace(/%Y%/g,y);
4174 		path=path.replace(/%WL%/g,w);
4175 		path=path.replace(/%WS%/g,ws);
4176 		path=path.replace(/%F%/g,f);
4177 		top.setAttribute("d",path);
4178 		top.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
4179 			if(tn)
4180 			{
4181 				top.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
4182 			}
4183 			else
4184 			{	
4185 				desc = "LENGTH: %W% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
4186 				desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
4187 				desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(f));
4188 				createDescription(id+"_header",desc);
4189 			}
4190 	}
4191 	// bottom
4192 	var bot = drawing.getElementById(id+"_threshold");
4193 	if(bot === null)
4194 	{
4195 		bot = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS ,"path");
4196 		bot.setAttribute("id",id+"_threshold");
4197 		bot.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
4198 		bot.setAttribute("class","frame");
4199 		
4200 		grp.appendChild(bot);
4201 	}
4202 	path = "M %X%,%Y% l %WL%,0 l 0,-%F% l -%WL%,0 l 0,%F%";
4203 	path=path.replace(/%X%/g,x);
4204 	path=path.replace(/%Y%/g,y+h);
4205 	path=path.replace(/%WL%/g,w);
4206 	path=path.replace(/%WS%/g,ws);
4207 	path=path.replace(/%F%/g,f/2);
4208 	bot.setAttribute("d",path);
4209 	bot.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");
4210 	if(tn)
4211 	{
4212 		bot.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
4213 	}
4214 	else
4215 	{
4216 		desc = "LENGTH: %W% ... Mitred 45% %F% extrusion stock.";
4217 		desc = desc.replace(/%W%/g,inchesToInchesDim(w));
4218 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(f));
4219 		createDescription(id+"_threshold",desc);
4220 	}
4221 	
4222 	// left
4223 	var left = drawing.getElementById(id+"_left_jamb");
4224 	if(left === null)
4225 	{
4226 		left = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"path");
4227 		left.setAttribute("id",id+"_left_jamb");
4228 		left.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
4229 		left.setAttribute("class","frame");
4230 		
4231 		grp.appendChild(left);
4232 	}
4233 	
4234 	path = "M %X%,%Y% l 0,%HL% l %F%,0 l 0,-%HS% l -%F%,-%F%";
4235 	path=path.replace(/%X%/g,x);
4236 	path=path.replace(/%Y%/g,y);
4237 	path=path.replace(/%HL%/g,h-(f/2));
4238 	path=path.replace(/%HS%/g,hs+(f/2));
4239 	path=path.replace(/%F%/g,f);
4240 	left.setAttribute("d",path);
4241 	left.getStyle().setProperty("fill",color,"");

4243 	{
4244 		left.setAttribute("class","frameTN");
4245 	}
4246 	else

4249 		desc = desc.replace(/%H%/g,inchesToInchesDim(h));
4250 		desc = desc.replace(/%F%/g,inchesToInchesDim(f));
4251 		createDescription(id+"_left_jamb",desc);
4252 	}
4253 	
4254 	// right
4255 	var right = drawing.getElementById(id+"_right_jamb");
4256 	if(right === null)
4257 	{
4258 		right = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS, "path");
4259 		right.setAttribute("id",id+"_right_jamb");
4260 		right.setAttribute("d","M 0,0");
4261 		right.setAttribute("class","frame");
4262 		
4263 		grp.appendChild(right);
4264 	}
4265 	path = "M %X%,%Y% l 0,%HL% l -%F%,0 l 0,-%HS% l %F%,-%F%";

4473 /**
4474  * Draw a non-mitred 3-sided door frame.
4475  * 
4476  * @param id		String id
4477  * @param x			decimal x coordinate
4478  * @param y			decimal y coordinate
4479  * @param w			decimal width
4480  * @param h			decimal height
4481  * @param f			decimal side frame thickness
4482  * @param fTop		decimal top frame thickness
4483  * @param color		String web color code
4484  * @return
4485  */
4486 function initDoorNoThresholdNonMtrdFrame(id, x, y, w, h, f, fTop, color)
4487 {
4488 try
4489 {
4490 trace("initDoorNoThresholdNonMtrdFrame('"+id+"',"+x+","+ y+","+ w+","+ h+","+ f+","+ fTop+",'"+ color+"')");
4491

4496 
4497

4500 	if(grp == null)
4501 	{
4502 		grp = drawing.createElementNS(svgNS,"g");
4503 		grp.setAttribute("id",id);
4504 		drawing.getElementById("window").appendChild(grp);
4505 	}

4509 	{
